cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with the manual annotation of pictures with WordNet synsets, which is a natural language processing task. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) because the tool allows for keyword searching and attaching of synsets to pictures, which is a form of information retrieval. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) because the tool could potentially be used to train machine learning models on affective picture recognition. It could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) because the GAPED pictures being annotated are likely to be visual stimuli. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) because the tool is designed to be user-friendly and efficient for manual annotation.
